FOOD POISONING - SAUDI ARABIA (JIZAN): REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
*************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
Date: Fri, 4 Feb 2005
From: Shamsudeen Fagbo and ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Saudi Gazette [edited]
<http://www.saudigazette.com.sa/sgazette/Data/2005/2/4/Art_186968.XML>

Food poisoning cases reported
--------------------------------
Al-Aridhah General Hospital in Jizan Region received 19 suspected food
poisoning cases who fell ill after taking meals from a restaurant,
according to Okaz. The cases including a woman suffered from severe
diarrhea, abdominal pain, vomiting and dizziness. The restaurant was closed
down and 3 of its workers were detained pending the results of laboratory
tests.
A committee was formed including a representative of Al-Aridhah
Governorate, a health supervisor from the municipality, the director of
primary health care, and a representative of the Infections Combat
Department in Al-Aridhah Hospital.
16 persons were released from hospital after receiving treatment whereas 3
others are still hospitalized.
The report of the committee pointed out that the inspection tour of the
restaurant carried out by the municipality on 16 Jan 2005 revealed some
hygienic violations.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[More information is needed -- regarding the incubation period, food eaten,
and the presence or absence of fever -- before we can speculate on the
cause of this illness. - Mod.LL]
